As my comment has helped you, I&#39;m gonna leave it as an answer. It might be useful for someone else &#128521;

---

Action handlers are invoked outside of the Angular zone. This is by design and controlled via &quot;execution strategy&quot;. By default NGXS uses the `DispatchOutsideZoneNgxsExecutionStrategy`. It executes your code outside of the Angular zone via `runOutsideAngular` in the browser.

All you&#39;ve got to do is to invoke the `translate.use` method inside the Angular&#39;s zone:

&lt;!-- language: typescript --&gt;

    this.ngZone.run(() =&gt; this.translate.use(action.lang));

Don&#39;t forget to inject the `NgZone` class.

---

