The `card` element has an `update` method that can be used to pass to it the same options as when first creating it. By using an event listener with the `update` methods, one can change the font-size in just the same way as it was first defined.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    window.addEventListener(&#39;resize&#39;, function(event) {
      if (window.innerWidth &lt;= 320) {
        card.update({style: {base: {fontSize: &#39;13px&#39;}}});
      } else {
        card.update({style: {base: {fontSize: &#39;16px&#39;}}});
      }
    });

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Source: https://stripe.com/docs/stripe-js/reference#other-methods

